[Data by country, area, or territory for 21 Apr 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20Apr21_1619118588.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 19.6% of daily case numbers and 29.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 60.06 million cases. The USA reported over 56 000 cases over the last 24 hours followed by Brazil with 30 624 cases, Argentina (20 461), Columbia (14 189), and Canada (10 275); 10 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Peru, Mexico, Chile, Paraguay, Guatemala, Puerto Rico, Bolivia Uruguay, Venezuela, and Cuba). An additional 3 countries (Honduras, Ecuador, and Costa Rica) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 29.1% of daily case numbers and 37.4% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 49.82 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (1 case), Switzerland (3 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others. Turkey reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by France, Germany, Poland, Ukraine and Italy, reporting more than 10 000 new cases in the past 24 hours. Another 17 countries reported more than 1000 cases, and an additional 9 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 7.3% of daily case numbers and 8.2% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 8.60 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (25 492) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, Jordan, Tunisia, Palestinian Authority, UAE, Lebanon, Kuwait, Oman, Saudi Arabia, and Bahrain. Morocco, Libya, Qatar, and Egypt reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 0.8% of daily case numbers and 2.2% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.24 million cases. Ethiopia (1524) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours. South Africa and Kenya reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Botswana, and Gabon, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 4.2% of daily case numbers and 2.4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 2.25 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 16 000 cases), followed by Japan, Malaysia, Mongolia, and South Korea.

- The South East Asia region reported 39.0% of the daily newly reported cases and 20.4% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 18.56 million cases. India is dominant reporting over 295 000 cases, followed by Indonesia (5549), Bangladesh (4559), Nepal (1667), Thailand (1458), and Sri Lanka (367).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 21 April 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

